vulnerability.name: USN-6361-2
vulnerability.description: USN-6361-1 fixed a vulnerability in CUPS. This update provides the corresponding updates for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS and Ubuntu 18.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that CUPS incorrectly authenticated certain remote  requests. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to obtain  recently printed documents.

statements.status_notes: CUPS could be made to expose sensitive information. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
